    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">A project report on surveillance and bomb detection robot used in war field</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Misra, Rishabh<br />Rai, Sahil<br />Koshy, Samson</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">surveillance and bomb detection<br />robot used in war field</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">1-May-2013 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Srm University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P6047</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">In today’s world technological warfare has become a need and many devices and machines are being built to reduce casualties. Our project deals with just this, it basically is a concept of robots helping the army to provide them with knowledge about land mines and enemy soldiers well before entering into a war field. This concept can be used and many other variations can be brought in.
The robot uses three basic sensors that are, 1.RFID reader, 2.PIR sensor and 3.Metal detector. The PIR sensor senses the presence of a human being. The RFID reader checks if the soldier is ours or an enemy soldier and the metal detector detects whether it’s a soldier (since a soldier carries some amount of metal) or a bomb\land mine. The movement of the robot is done through a computer.
The basic requirements of the robot were an assembly program, a logical algorithm, all the sensors, wheels, motors, bus wires etc. A lot of planning and hard work has been put in to making this project a success. All the parts can be fabricated with the help of basic tools which can be found in any workshop. The main advantage of this robot is the number of lives it saves it is a concept by which spying is made easy and we are sure that such robots will be used on a full scale in the years to come</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/17493">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/17493</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/17020">Mech-2013</a><br/></td></tr>
</table></center><br/>
